titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the Auditing Office, Yale University, Records
titlestmt.author: compiled by Daniel Hartwig

publicationstmt.publisher: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on Friday January 11, 2019 at 08:00

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of reports, subject files, and memoranda of the Yale Auditing Office. The records document salaries, investments, fellowships, building and maintenance funds, insurance, payroll and benefits, and research expenses.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 5-E (YRG 5-E), Auditing records of Yale University.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the records is restricted to the office of origin only.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Auditing Office, Yale University, Records (RU 169). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged by accession.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of reports, subject files, and memoranda of the Yale Auditing Office. The records document salaries, investments, fellowships, building and maintenance funds, insurance, payroll and benefits, and research expenses.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Restricted to office of origin only.
